      "category": "team",
      "content": "A vulnerability was present in the ████████████ website that allows an authenticated user to delete animals belonging to other users' accounts. This issue arises due to an Insecure Direct Object Reference (IDOR) vulnerability where the system's authorization mechanism fails to properly validate and restrict access to protected resources based on the user's identity. As a result, a malicious user can manipulate the ██████████████ parameter in the request sent to the ████████████████ endpoint to delete any animal from other users' accounts, leading to unauthorized data deletion.",
